th `.strip()` — `auth` needs the same treatment. Severity: **blocking** (same root cause as #1).\n\nWait, let me re-check the host handling pattern more carefully. Line 578: `host_raw = _clean_secret(gateway_blob.get(\"host\")).strip()` then line 619: `host=host_raw or \"0.0.0.0\"`. The `.strip()` ensures `\"   \"` → `\"\"` → `\"0.0.0.0\"` default. But for `auth`, line 623: `auth=_clean_secret(auth_raw)` — no `.strip()`, and `GatewayInputs.auth` has no default/fallback. A whitespace-only auth stays truthy.\n\n\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 2,\n  \"summary\": \"All four review-1 items (B1, B2, W1, W5) are resolved. However, a new whitespace-only token bypass is introduced: the dict-path validation at line 604 checks `not token` which accepts whitespace-only strings like `\\\"   \\\"`, and neither the dict-path nor the bare-string path applies `.strip()` before `_clean_secret` — the same defense that exists for `gateway.host`. A whitespace-only auth token violates the #437 gateway-token invariant the same way an empty one would.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:604\",\n      \"issue\": \"Whitespace-only string token in dict form bypasses validation. `not isinstance(token, str) or not token` accepts `\\\"   \\\"` because it is a truthy non-empty str. After `_clean_secret` (which strips NUL/CR/LF but not spaces/tabs), `GatewayInputs.auth=\\\"   \\\"` flows to `_render_openclaw_json` which emits `{\\\"mode\\\": \\\"token\\\", \\\"token\\\": \\\"   \\\"}` — a no-auth gateway violating the #437 invariant. The `gateway.host` field has an explicit `.strip()` before the `or \\\"0.0.0.0\\\"` default (line 578), but `auth` has no equivalent stripping.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add `.strip()` before the emptiness check, mirroring the host-field pattern: `if not isinstance(token, str) or not token.strip():`. For the bare-string path, also apply `.strip()` to `auth_raw` before `_clean_secret`